text:
(1)
2319 King's Highway, north side, between Delamere (East 23rd Street) and Mansfield Place (East 24th Street), showing the estate of Judge Terhune of South Greenfield who erected this house in 1812. Benjamin G. Hitchings purchased it at about 1860. It was demolished in 1928. His estate which comprised 1092 lots was sold on October 11, 1897.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, looking northwest.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, front view.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4)
The same, another angle.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

text:
2319 King's Highway, north side, between Delamare and Mansfield Places, showing the home of Judge Terhune, later owned by B.G. Hitchings. It was erected in 1812, and demolished in 1929.
1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
